The '''Amilcar CGSS''' or '''CGSs''' was a sporting car made by the [[Amilcar]] company from 1926 to 1929. The second ''S'' stood for surbaisse and the car was a lowered version of the [[Amilcar CGS|CGS]].

The 1074&nbsp;cc four cylinder engine from the CGS was fitted but in a slightly higher state of tune.

4700 were made.

